 CORS withCredentials Session Hijacking via cors_exploit_poc.html (Operation Escaneo)

In this threat hunting scenario, we searched for activities related to CORS exploitation and session token harvesting, including the creation or access of suspicious files such as cors_exploit_poc.html and the use of tools like PowerShell, curl, or wget to interact with authentication-related artifacts such as AMAUTHID and SAT.

The objective was to identify attempts to abuse CORS misconfigurations and the withCredentials functionality to steal web session tokens, hijack user sessions, and gain unauthorized access to applications. Successful exploitation could lead to account takeover, data exposure, and further compromise of internal resources

